      ],
      "summary": "Penny Appeal USA is a humanitarian organization <cite id=\"1\">founded in 2016</cite> that focuses on alleviating poverty through sustainable development and emergency relief. The organization has demonstrated significant growth, reporting <cite id=\"2\">$10,943,897 in total revenue</cite> for the 2023 fiscal year, representing a <cite id=\"3\">3-year revenue CAGR of 10.9%</cite>. Their operations span across <cite id=\"4\">multiple countries including Palestine, Yemen, and Syria</cite>, where they deliver essential services through programs such as Feed Our World and Thirst Relief. The charity maintains a high level of institutional trust, evidenced by a <cite id=\"5\">99/100 overall score from Charity Navigator</cite> and a <cite id=\"6\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite>. Financially, the organization is characterized by strong fundraising efficiency, spending only <cite id=\"7\">$0.14 to raise every $1</cite>, which is significantly better than many industry peers. While their <cite id=\"8\">program expense ratio of 74.3%</cite> is lower than the peer median, they maintain <cite id=\"9\">5.7 months of working capital</cite>, ensuring operational resilience in volatile humanitarian contexts. For Muslim donors, the organization provides a <cite id=\"10\">verified zakat-eligible platform</cite> that serves all eight asnaf categories, including the poor and needy.",
